# Linear Webhooks

Webhooks enable real-time event-driven automation. When resources change in Linear, an HTTP POST is sent to your endpoint with the event payload.

## Creating a Webhook

### Via GraphQL API

```graphql
mutation CreateWebhook {
  webhookCreate(input: {
    url: "https://your-app.com/webhooks/linear"
    resourceTypes: ["Issue", "Comment", "Project"]
    teamId: "TEAM_UUID"
    label: "My Integration"
  }) {
    success
    webhook {
      id
      url
      enabled
      secret
    }
  }
}
```

Omit `teamId` to receive events for all public teams.

### Via Linear Settings

1. Go to Settings → API → Webhooks
2. Click **New webhook**
3. Enter your endpoint URL
4. Select resource types
5. Optionally scope to a specific team
6. Save — note the signing secret

## Supported Resource Types

| Resource | Events | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| `Issue` | create, update, remove | Issue lifecycle events |
| `Comment` | create, update, remove | Issue comments |
| `IssueLabel` | create, update, remove | Label changes |
| `Project` | create, update, remove | Project lifecycle |
| `ProjectUpdate` | create, update, remove | Project status updates |
| `Cycle` | create, update, remove | Sprint/cycle events |
| `Reaction` | create, remove | Comment reactions |
| `Document` | create, update, remove | Document changes |
| `Initiative` | create, update, remove | Initiative events |
| `InitiativeUpdate` | create, update, remove | Initiative status updates |
| `Customer` | create, update, remove | Customer records |
| `CustomerRequest` | create, update, remove | Customer requests |
| `User` | update | User profile changes |
| `IssueSLA` | — | SLA-related events |

## Payload Structure

```json
{
  "action": "create",
  "type": "Issue",
  "createdAt": "2026-04-11T10:30:00.000Z",
  "webhookTimestamp": 1744367400000,
  "data": {
    "id": "issue-uuid",
    "identifier": "ENG-42",
    "title": "Bug: login fails on Safari",
    "priority": 2,
    "state": { "id": "state-uuid", "name": "In Progress", "type": "started" },
    "assignee": { "id": "user-uuid", "name": "Jane Dev" },
    "team": { "id": "team-uuid", "key": "ENG" },
    "labelIds": ["label-uuid"],
    "url": "https://linear.app/my-org/issue/ENG-42"
  },
  "actor": {
    "id": "user-uuid",
    "name": "Jane Dev",
    "type": "user"
  },
  "updatedFrom": null
}
```

For `update` actions, `updatedFrom` contains the previous values of changed fields.

## HTTP Headers

| Header | Purpose |
|--------|----------|
| `Linear-Delivery` | Unique UUID for this delivery |
| `Linear-Event` | Resource type (e.g., `Issue`) |
| `Linear-Signature` | HMAC-SHA256 signature for verification |
| `Content-Type` | `application/json` |

## Signature Verification

Verify that payloads are genuinely from Linear using HMAC-SHA256:

```typescript
import { createHmac, timingSafeEqual } from "crypto";

function verifyWebhookSignature(
  body: string,
  signature: string,
  secret: string
): boolean {
  const hmac = createHmac("sha256", secret);
  hmac.update(body);
  const digest = hmac.digest("hex");

  const sigBuffer = Buffer.from(signature, "utf8");
  const digestBuffer = Buffer.from(digest, "utf8");

  if (sigBuffer.length !== digestBuffer.length) return false;
  return timingSafeEqual(sigBuffer, digestBuffer);
}
```

**Also verify the timestamp** — reject payloads where `webhookTimestamp` is more than 60 seconds old to prevent replay attacks.

## Express.js Webhook Handler

```typescript
import express from "express";
import { createHmac, timingSafeEqual } from "crypto";

const app = express();
const WEBHOOK_SECRET = process.env.LINEAR_WEBHOOK_SECRET!;

app.post("/webhooks/linear", express.raw({ type: "application/json" }), (req, res) => {
  const signature = req.headers["linear-signature"] as string;
  const body = req.body.toString();

  // Verify signature
  const hmac = createHmac("sha256", WEBHOOK_SECRET);
  hmac.update(body);
  const digest = hmac.digest("hex");

  const sigBuf = Buffer.from(signature, "utf8");
  const digBuf = Buffer.from(digest, "utf8");

  if (sigBuf.length !== digBuf.length || !timingSafeEqual(sigBuf, digBuf)) {
    return res.status(401).send("Invalid signature");
  }

  // Verify timestamp (reject if > 60s old)
  const payload = JSON.parse(body);
  const age = Date.now() - payload.webhookTimestamp;
  if (age > 60_000) {
    return res.status(401).send("Stale webhook");
  }

  // Process the event
  const { action, type, data } = payload;
  console.log(`${type} ${action}: ${data.identifier || data.id}`);

  switch (type) {
    case "Issue":
      if (action === "create") {
        console.log(`New issue: ${data.identifier} — ${data.title}`);
      } else if (action === "update" && payload.updatedFrom?.stateId) {
        console.log(`Issue ${data.identifier} state changed to ${data.state.name}`);
      }
      break;
    case "Comment":
      if (action === "create") {
        console.log(`New comment on ${data.issue?.identifier}`);
      }
      break;
  }

  res.status(200).send("OK");
});

app.listen(3000, () => console.log("Webhook handler listening on :3000"));
```

## Requirements

- Endpoint must be **publicly accessible via HTTPS**
- Must respond with **HTTP 200** within **5 seconds**
- Failed deliveries retry at 1 minute, 1 hour, and 6 hours
- Persistent failures may disable the webhook automatically

## Linear IP Addresses

For IP allowlisting, Linear sends webhooks from:
- `35.231.147.226`
- `35.243.134.228`
- `34.140.253.14`
- `34.38.87.206`
- `34.134.222.122`
- `35.222.25.142`

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|----------|
| `LINEAR_API_KEY` | API key for creating webhooks via GraphQL |
| `LINEAR_WEBHOOK_SECRET` | Signing secret for signature verification |
| `LINEAR_WEBHOOK_URL` | Your webhook endpoint URL |
